{({{\rm{K}}_{{\rm{sp}}}}{\rm{MS}}\, = 5 \times {{10}^{ - 21}},{{\rm{K}}_{\rm{1}}}({{\rm{H}}_{\rm{2}}}{\rm{S}}) = {{10}^7},}\\
{{\mkern 1mu} {{\rm{K}}_{\rm{2}}}({{\rm{H}}_{\rm{2}}}{\rm{S}}) = {{10}^{ - 14}}).}
\end{array}$

explanation:
After mixing,<br>$\begin{array}{l}
\left[ {{\rm{A}}{{\rm{g}}^{\rm{ + }}}} \right] = (1/2) \times {10^{ - 4}} = 5 \times {10^{ - 5}}{\rm{M}}\\
\left[ {{\rm{C}}{{\rm{l}}^ - }} \right] = (1/2) \times {10^{ - 4}} = 5 \times {10^{ - 5}}{\rm{M}}\\
{{\rm{K}}_{{\rm{sp }}}} = \left[ {{\rm{A}}{{\rm{g}}^{\rm{ + }}}} \right]\left[ {{\rm{C}}{{\rm{l}}^ - }} \right] = {\left( {5 \times {{10}^{ - 5}}} \right)^2}\\
\quad  = 2.5 \times {10^{ - 9}}
\end{array}$<br>Since, ionic product is greater than solubility product, hence precipitation will take place.

